comments: Anunoby (NYK) briefly grasps Embiid's (PHI) arm and marginal contact occurs before Embiid receives the post-entry pass.
Maxey (PHI) slides his hand off Achiuwa's (NYK) shoulder and marginal contact occurs as Maxey releases away at the end of the drive.
Hart (NYK) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Harris (PHI) reaches across and initiates contact with Brunson's (NYK) wrist, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Maxey (PHI) steps inside the three-point arc and does not re-establish himself outside of it before Brunson (NYK) releases his free throw attempt.
Anunoby (NYK) cleanly dislodges the ball from Lowry (PHI) and is the last player to touch it before it goes out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to the 76ers.
Lowry (PHI) establishes himself in Achiuwa's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as both players mutually engage during the pick.
Achiuwa (NYK) legally contests Oubre Jr.'s (PHI) jump shot attempt.
Lowry (PHI) removes his resting arms from Brunson's (NYK) body and marginal contact occurs as he releases away to secure the long rebound.
Hart (NYK) legally contests Harris' (PHI) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) makes clean hand-on-ball contact to dislodge it from Anunoby (NYK) during the rebound.
Embiid (PHI) brings his arm toward Brunson's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs before Brunson makes his intended pass on the perimeter.
Maxey (PHI) avoids making any illegal contact with Brunson (NYK) as Brunson's own feet come together and get briefly tangled as he elevates during the driving shot attempt.
Lowry (PHI) establishes himself in Anunoby's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the screen.
Anunoby (NYK) initiates contact with Embiid's (PHI) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Batum (PHI) grasps Achiuwa's (NYK) jersey and marginal contact occurs as they mutually engage off-ball during the inbound.
Hart (NYK) gathers the ball on his right foot and hops consecutively on it before passing.
Brunson (NYK) legally lifts his pivot foot and releases his pass attempt before his pivot foot returns to the ground.
Batum (PHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.

Embiid (PHI) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Hart (NYK) during the drive. After coming to a stop, Hart fumbles the ball on his own accord as he attempts to pass and any contact as both players pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.
Brunson (NYK) retreats alongside Maxey's (PHI) path and maintains a legal guarding position before making clean contact with the ball to dislodge it during the driving shot attempt.

Lowry (PHI) firms up in a screening position in Anunoby's (NYK) path and is dislodged from his legally obtained position before the ball is inbounded.  An away-from-the-play foul is correctly assessed.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) does not establish himself in Anunoby's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as Anunoby maintains his defensive matchup during the screen.

Replay review of the out of bounds called on Brunson (NYK) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. There was no clear or conclusive video evidence to overturn the call on the court of Brunson touching the ball last before it went out of bounds.

Achiuwa (NYK) is retracting his arm away from Embiid (PHI) as he absorbs the marginal contact and makes contact with the ball to partially block the shot attempt at the basket. Any additional contact to Embiid's lower body is a result of the marginal contact.
Embiid (PHI) initiates illegal contact with Hart's (NYK) arms as he attempts to tie up the ball.
Batum (PHI) grasps McBride's (NYK) jersey and marginal contact occurs during the pursuit of the rebound.
Lowry (PHI) establishes himself in McBride's (NYK) path and does not extend into McBride as marginal contact occurs when McBride goes under the hand-off pick.
Lowry (PHI) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg out as incidental contact occurs with Brunson (NYK) during the jump shot attempt.
McBride (NYK) initiates contact with Lowry's (PHI) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
During the rebound, Achiuwa (NYK) and Batum (PHI) mutually engage and marginal contact occurs as both players pursue the loose ball.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) commits a take foul on Brunson (NYK).
During the inbound, Brunson (NYK) and Lowry (PHI) mutually engage and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Anunoby (NYK) legally contests Embiid's (PHI) jump shot attempt.
